  <span id="freeText12198282234377725618" style="display:none"><i>Just listen, Adam says with a voice that sounds like shrapnel.<br /><br />I open my eyes wide now.<br />I sit up as much as I can.<br />And I listen.<br /><br />Stay, he says.</i><br /><br />Choices. Seventeen-year-old Mia is faced with some tough ones: Stay true to her first love—music—even if it means losing her boyfriend and leaving her family and friends behind?<br /><br />Then one February morning Mia goes for a drive with her family, and in an instant, everything changes. Suddenly, all the choices are gone, except one. And it's the only one that matters.<br /><br /><i>If I Stay</i> is a heartachingly beautiful book about the power of love, the true meaning of family, and the choices we all make.<br /><br /><i>Librarian note: an alternate cover for this edition can be found <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/21570677-if-i-stay" rel="nofollow noopener">here</a>.</i></span>
